<paragraph blockId="306.[151,1436,873,1042]" box="[151,947,873,898]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">
<collectingCountry box="[151,262,873,898]" name="Argentina" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">Argentina</collectingCountry>
records for 36 species in five genera have been encountered.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="306.[151,1436,873,1042]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307">
This group was treated as a subfamily of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Packauskas" authorityYear="1994" box="[714,818,909,934]" class="Insecta" family="Coreidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Coreidae</taxonomicName>
, often earlier with the name 
<taxonomicName box="[1146,1259,909,934]" class="Insecta" family="Coreidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Corizinae">Corizinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chopra" box="[1271,1436,909,934]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" refString="Chopra, N. P. (1967) The higher classification of the family Rhopalidae (Hemiptera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 119, 363 - 399. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1967. tb 00503. x" type="journal article" year="1967">Chopra (1967)</bibRefCitation>
presented 
<taxonomicName box="[265,375,945,970]" class="Insecta" family="Cydnidae" genus="Aethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="306" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="revision">a revision</taxonomicName>
of the higher classification of this family and included keys to subfamilies, tribes, and genera, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gollner-Scheiding" box="[151,440,981,1006]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" refString="Gollner-Scheiding, U. (1983) General-kataloge der Familie Rhopalidae (Heteroptera). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 59, 37 - 189." type="journal article" year="1983">Göllner-Scheiding (1983)</bibRefCitation>
published a World catalog of the family. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schaefer" box="[919,1100,981,1006]" pageId="306" pageNumber="307" refString="Schaefer, C. E. (1993) The Pentatomomorpha (Hemiptera: Heteroptera): An annotated outline of its systematic history. European Journal of Entomology, 90, 105 - 122." type="journal article" year="1993">Schaefer (1993)</bibRefCitation>
has written about the origins and biogeography of the New World fauna.
</paragraph>
